The paper deals with a data structure for supporting range maximum-sum segment queries, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also discusses space lower bounds, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The application of the data structure to finding k-covers involves optimization, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
